The White House has issued a statement condemning the use of violence against citizens who are demonstrating in Syria. They applaud the courage and dignity of the Syrian people and urge all parties to remain calm and avoid violence. The Syrian government is called upon to respect human rights and allow peaceful demonstrations. President Bashar al-Assad is urged to take concrete steps towards meaningful reform. The statement emphasizes that violence is not the solution to the grievances of the Syrian people, and what is needed now is a credible path towards a future of greater freedom, democracy, opportunity, and justice.